{%- comment -%}
  Checkbox / radio (spec §5.3). One snippet for both since they differ only in
  `type` and the visual glyph (checkmark vs. dot) — same label-wrapping structure,
  same 44px clickable row.

  Wrapping the native input WITH the visual box AND the text inside one <label>
  is deliberate: it makes the entire row clickable (spec: "Labels are full
  clickable rows in filter contexts") without any JS, and the native input stays
  in the accessibility tree and keyboard-operable — the visual box is a sibling
  <span aria-hidden="true">, never a replacement for the real control.

  Accepts:
  - id (required), name (required), label (required)
  - kind: 'checkbox' (default) | 'radio'
  - value: input value (relevant for radio groups / checkbox arrays)
  - checked (bool), required (bool)
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign field_kind = kind | default: 'checkbox'
-%}
<label class="checkbox-field checkbox-field--{{ field_kind }}" for="{{ id }}">
  <input
    class="checkbox-field__input"
    type="{{ field_kind }}"
    id="{{ id }}"
    name="{{ name }}"
    {% if value %}value="{{ value }}"{% endif %}
    {% if checked %}checked{% endif %}
    {% if required %}required aria-required="true"{% endif %}
  >
  <span class="checkbox-field__box" aria-hidden="true">
    {%- if field_kind != 'radio' -%}
      {% render 'icon', name: 'check', size: 14, class: 'checkbox-field__check' %}
    {%- endif -%}
  </span>
  <span class="checkbox-field__label">{{ label }}</span>
</label>
